This bit caused a lot of wasted time trying to figure out why the response was not working. I had to use the deprecated form since the form above gave incorrect results - the json was mangled with some extra characters and I'm not sure where those occurred. Initially I assumed it's a compressed stream but it's not since the source is always uncompressed from the underlying object.
So maybe it's stored in JSON format ... don't know.
@imotov any ideas?

